<title type="html"><![CDATA[2/28 (Thu) Midlife-When We Want Happiness Now/How to be happy every day(Host:Nikki)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=259&amp;p=275#p275"><![CDATA[
Session 1: “Midlife- When We Want Happiness Now” <br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/the-intelligent-divorce/201603/midlife-when-we-want-happiness-now?eml">https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/th ... ss-now?eml</a><!-- m --> <br /><br />Questions: <br />1. What stage of life do you think you are in now?  How is it different from the previous stage, both inside and outside?<br /><br />2. Is your identity changed through different stages of your life? How?<br /><br />3. How do you confront the aging self?<br /><br />4. What is the un-lived life that is calling out to you, if there is one?<br /><br /><br /><br />Session 2: How to be happy every day: it will change the world. <br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/78nsxRxbf4w">https://youtu.be/78nsxRxbf4w</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Extended reading: “5 Ways Giving is Good for you”<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://greatergood.berkeley.edu/article/item/5_ways_giving_is_good_for_you">https://greatergood.berkeley.edu/articl ... od_for_you</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions: <br />1. Are you a happy person？What makes you happy?<br /><br />2. Do you agree giving makes the giver happy？ Why or why not？<br /><br />3. What do you feel when giving? Give one or two examples. <br /><br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />8:10 ~ 8:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:25 ~ 8:30pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:30 ~9:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Fri Feb 22, 2019 10:33 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
